      {
        "name": "My name is Knox!",
        "species": "Dog",
        "breed": "German Shepherd Dog",
        "age": "Unknown",
        "gender": "Unknown",
        "bio": "All around me are dogs who are at different stages of acclimating to shelter life; some are brave and make it look easy and some are just trying to right the world that has been turned upside down. Here's the thing, I'm having a hard time. The people I used to love, the dog I used to be, the life I used to know; all of that's gone and I've had to start over new. I tell you this so that you know to take things slow and give me grace when we meet; I've never had to do this before. I'm a loyal and independent girl who would prefer to be the only pet in a quiet household. I need only a few things but very consistently; food/water, love and exercise. Maybe you too have been through a difficult time and felt misunderstood? I'm hoping you're the person who can give me everything that I need and that I may return the favor, too.Less",
        "photo": null,
        "url": "https://www.adoptapet.com/pet/47593433-wausau-wisconsin-german-shepherd-dog-mix"
      },
      {
        "name": "My name is Muntz!",
        "species": "Dog",
        "breed": "Labrador Retriever",
        "age": "Unknown",
        "gender": "Unknown",
        "bio": "COURTESY POST This dog is not in our Rescue, but Fetch is assisting with the screening of applicants. Meet Muntz! Muntz is a spirited 3-year-old mix (think some kind of herding mix crossed with Lab!) weighing in at a sturdy 60 lbs. This handsome, neutered boy is fully vaccinated and ready to find his forever home — he just needs the right fit. His best qualities: Muntz is a people lover through and through. He’ll greet you at the door with enthusiastic jumps and a wagging tail — his excitement is contagious! He’s crate-trained, has zero accidents indoors, and is highly food-motivated, making him a great candidate for training. He also loves toys and keeping his mouth busy with a good chew. What makes Muntz tick: True to his herding roots, Muntz has a sharp mind and a big heart. He wants to know what everyone is doing at all times — and he’d love nothing more than a job to do. Give him a purpose, some room to run, and consistent training, and he will be your most devoted right-hand man. His ideal home: Muntz thrives with experienced dog owners who understand herding breeds. He does best without young children, as he doesn’t quite know his size and can get mouthy when excited. He can coexist with other dogs that have calm, passive temperaments. His status with cats and small animals is unknown. What Muntz needs from you: Room to run and burn energy An owner who enjoys training and engagement A calm, structured home environment Lots of love and quality time with his people If yo",
        "photo": null,
        "url": "https://www.adoptapet.com/pet/47508378-wausau-wisconsin-labrador-retriever-mix"
      },
      {
        "name": "My name is Walter!",
        "species": "Dog",
        "breed": "Pit Bull Terrier / Basset Hound",
        "age": "Unknown",
        "gender": "Unknown",
        "bio": "Hey! I’m Walter! I’ve been with Fetch for awhile now, and I’m STILL looking for my forever family. Let me reintroduce myself: I’m a happy boy who likes to be a part of what’s going on. Whether we’re making dinner, you’re showering, or doing laundry - doesn’t matter to me as long as we’re together. I can supervise any project you got goin on! I am always excited to show you what I have. I am kennel/crate trained and I know to do my business outside! I’m strong, like you can tell I work out and all that. I know how to walk nicely on a leash but sometimes I seriously forget it’s even attached, this nose of mine is soooo powerful it’s crazy. I am special, my foster mom says it all the time. Just to make sure I get enough love and attention, it would be best if I am the only “good boy” in my forever home. I run like a graceful rhino and my white hair is so silky soft you won’t be able to resist loving on me. I have gotten myself into a couple situations and I really want to leave my troubled past behind me and move forward with people who get me. People who know tell me that I need structure and leadership: if you let me be the pack leader, I will take advantage of that situation. I love training and learning, my foster mom is kick butt cool at it, she has lots more information for you since I am sooo special, so apply and let’s get this party started! Apply here: https://www.fetchfosterandrescue.com/adopt Name: Walter Sex: Male Breed: Pitbull/Basset Hound mix Age: 4 years Weight:",
