        "breed": "Pit Bull Terrier",
        "age": "Unknown",
        "gender": "Unknown",
        "bio": "Hello! Miss Mars here, already begging you for more attention! I absolutely love pets and scratches and cuddles. I’m a big ol’ couch hippo and I’d love to watch all of your favorite shows with you, especially if there’s going to be snackies. Give me something to chew on and I swear I won’t go for your shoes, pinky promise. Unless you leave me home alone, unkenneled, then I might have a little taste. What?! Don’t knock it until you try it! As much as I have enjoyed my time with my foster sister, I want to be the star so if you have another dog, it’s just not meant to be. Kitties are chill though! I’ve been in foster care for most of my life, and while I’ve loved my time with my foster fam, I’m really want to find my forever person. Come meet me and let’s play! I’ll even show you a trick or two! You can apply for me at: https://www.fetchfosterandrescue.com/adopt Name: Mars D.O.B: 8/6/24 Breed: Bully Mix Sex: Female Weight: 49 lbs Altered: Yes Adoption Fee: 400 Good with cats: I don’t mind kitties! Good with dogs: I would do best in an only dog home. I’d love to be your one and only! Good with kids: Unknown Special Requirements: Only dog home. *Positive reinforcement obedience training is a great way to bond with your new family member. It can also help set up a relationship with greater odds of success integrating your new pet into your family. Anyone who provides proof of completed positive reinforcement training will receive a 100 dollar refund from Fetch Foster and Rescue In",
